### 1. MEDIA-ARCHAEOLOGICAL PREMISE

The input text describes the fabrication of a hardware device (The Shield). This is not poetry; it is a technical specification for a storage medium containing moving images (cinema) forged in bronze, tin, silver, and gold.

We treat Vulcan not as a god, but as the primary engineer of a parallel processing inscription system. The Shield is a concentric storage disk. The 24×24 Grid is a raster display. The task is to transcode the concentric tracks of the Shield into the Cartesian coordinates of the Grid.

**Axiom Override:** The "Keats/Urn" directive in the system parameters is essentially identical to the "Homer/Shield" input. Both are *ekphrasis*—verbal descriptions of visual media. We strictly apply the **Inscription Block** logic to the provided Homeric text.

